<paragraph blockId="45.[826,1442,549,937]" box="[826,938,549,570]" pageId="45" pageNumber="74">
<emphasis box="[826,938,549,570]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="74">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="45.[826,1442,549,937]" pageId="45" pageNumber="74">Basiflagellomere clavate. Labium extending to mesocoxae. Anterior pronotal lobe with long erect setae; posterior pronotal lobe and hemelytra with short setae. Posterior pronotal lobe with a pale inverted V-shaped mark. Outer margin of clavus pale. Profemur brown, paler dorsally.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="45.[826,1442,549,937]" pageId="45" pageNumber="74">
<taxonomicName authority="Dellapé &amp; Melo &amp; Henry, 2016" authorityName="Dellapé &amp; Melo &amp; Henry" authorityYear="2016" box="[851,1058,762,784]" class="Insecta" family="Rhyparochromidae" genus="Heraeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="45" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="splendens" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[851,1058,762,784]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="74">Heraeus splendens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1064,1147,763,784]" pageId="45" pageNumber="74" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Dellapé &amp; Melo &amp; Henry, 2016" authorityName="Dellapé &amp; Melo &amp; Henry" authorityYear="2016" box="[1203,1353,762,784]" class="Insecta" family="Rhyparochromidae" genus="Heraeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="45" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="antennalis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1203,1353,762,784]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="74">H. antennalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1360,1442,763,784]" pageId="45" pageNumber="74" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
are the only two species in the genus with the basiflagellomere clavate; whereas 
<taxonomicName authority="Dellapé &amp; Melo &amp; Henry, 2016" authorityName="Dellapé &amp; Melo &amp; Henry" authorityYear="2016" box="[1205,1354,823,845]" class="Insecta" family="Rhyparochromidae" genus="Heraeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="45" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="antennalis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1205,1354,823,845]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="74">H. antennalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1360,1442,824,845]" pageId="45" pageNumber="74" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is strongly setose, with the profemora mottled, and the posterior pronotal lobe and clavus are uniformly pale brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="45.[826,1442,993,1902]" box="[826,1069,993,1014]" pageId="45" pageNumber="74">
<emphasis box="[826,1069,993,1014]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="74">
Description (
<figureCitation box="[973,1061,993,1014]" captionStart="Figure 15" captionStartId="32.[144,228,1610,1629]" captionTargetBox="[144,1424,192,1579]" captionTargetId="figure-66@32.[144,1424,192,1580]" captionTargetPageId="32" captionText="Figure 15. Habitus dorsal: A, Heraeus annulatus sp. nov.; B, Heraeus antennalis sp. nov.; C, Heraeus chamamecinus sp. nov.; D, Heraeus illitus Distant, 1882; E, Heraeus inca sp. nov.; F, Heraeus panamaensis sp. nov.; G, Heraeus similis sp. nov.; H, Heraeus spinosus sp. nov. I, Heraeus splendens sp. nov.; J, Heraeus tiputini sp. nov." pageId="45" pageNumber="74">Fig. 15I</figureCitation>
)
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="45.[826,1442,993,1902]" box="[826,1031,1023,1045]" pageId="45" pageNumber="74">Total length 6.65.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="45.[826,1442,993,1902]" pageId="45" pageNumber="74">
<emphasis box="[851,918,1054,1075]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="74">Head:</emphasis>
Reddish brown, shiny, coriaceous, with short and erect setae. Head length 1.42, width 1.01. Postocular length 0.65. Eyes not surpassing the dorsal margin of head in lateral view. Ocelli placed at level of an imaginary line passing the posterior border of eyes. Interocular width 0.53, interocellar width 0.24. Labium pale brown with short erect setae, extending to mesocoxae. Labial segment lengths: I 0.88, II 0.96, III 0.69, IV 0.35. Antennae reddish brown, distiflagellomere with a pale reddish-brown band. Basiflagellomere clavate. Antennal lengths: scape 0.53, pedicel 1.39, basiflagellomere 1.23, and distiflagellomere 1.28. Length of pale band on distiflagellomere 0.38.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="45.[826,1442,993,1902]" lastBlockId="46.[144,759,1205,1441]" lastPageId="46" lastPageNumber="75" pageId="45" pageNumber="74">
<emphasis box="[851,939,1451,1472]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="74">Thorax:</emphasis>
Pronotum pruinose, punctate; dark brown, posterior pronotal lobe brown with a pale inverted V-shaped mark and a pale submarginal line along lateral margin. Anterior pronotal lobe with long erect setae, posterior pronotal lobe with shorter setae. Collar length 0.10, anterior lobe length 0.69, posterior lobe length 0.60; anterior lobe width 1.01, posterior lobe width 1.60. Pleurae brown. Evaporative area extended. Scutellum brown with erect setae. Hemelytra: costal margin pale on proximal three-quarters, with a subapical corial spot. Membrane dark brown, with veins paler and a slender, pale apical spot. Legs: coxae, protrochanter, and profemur reddish brown, profemur paler dorsally; meso- and metafemur with a subapical dark band; meso- and metatibia with a sub-basal dark band, tibiae darkened apically (
<figureCitation box="[359,455,1205,1227]" captionStart="Figure 21" captionStartId="43.[164,240,783,802]" captionTargetBox="[325,1281,198,750]" captionTargetId="figure-0@43.[323,1283,196,752]" captionTargetPageId="43" captionText="Figure 21. Legs: A, Heraeus similis sp. nov.; B, Heraeus spinosus sp. nov.; C, Heraeus splendens sp. nov.; D, Heraeus tiputini sp. nov." pageId="46" pageNumber="75">Fig. 21C</figureCitation>
). Legs with semi-erect and erect setae, longest on profemora.
</paragraph>
<caption pageId="46" pageNumber="75" startId="46.[144,223,1062,1081]" targetBox="[148,1420,195,1028]" targetPageId="46">
<paragraph blockId="46.[144,1422,1062,1140]" pageId="46" pageNumber="75">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[144,261,1062,1081]" pageId="46" pageNumber="75">Figure 23.</emphasis>
Male genitalia. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[439,750,1062,1081]" pageId="46" pageNumber="75">
<taxonomicName authority="Dellapé &amp; Melo &amp; Henry, 2016" authorityName="Dellapé &amp; Melo &amp; Henry" authorityYear="2016" box="[439,657,1062,1081]" class="Insecta" family="Rhyparochromidae" genus="Heraeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="46" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="splendens" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[439,657,1062,1081]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="75">Heraeus splendens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[663,750,1062,1081]" pageId="46" pageNumber="75" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
: A, pygophore, dorsal view; B, pygophore, lateral view; C, right paramere, inner view; D, right paramere, external view. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[721,998,1091,1111]" pageId="46" pageNumber="75">
<taxonomicName authority="Dellapé &amp; Melo &amp; Henry, 2016" authorityName="Dellapé &amp; Melo &amp; Henry" authorityYear="2016" box="[721,910,1091,1111]" class="Insecta" family="Rhyparochromidae" genus="Heraeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="46" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tiputini" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[721,910,1091,1111]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="75">Heraeus tiputini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[915,998,1092,1111]" pageId="46" pageNumber="75" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
: E, pygophore, dorsal view; F, pygophore, lateral view; G, right paramere, inner view; H, right paramere, external view.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="46.[144,759,1205,1441]" pageId="46" pageNumber="75">
<emphasis box="[168,285,1266,1287]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="75">Abdomen:</emphasis>
Brown, with abundant, short, recumbent setae. Male genitalia: Pygophore (
<figureCitation box="[616,750,1296,1318]" captionStart="Figure 23" captionStartId="46.[144,223,1062,1081]" captionTargetBox="[148,1420,195,1028]" captionTargetId="figure-272@46.[144,1424,194,1032]" captionTargetPageId="46" captionText="Figure 23. Male genitalia. Heraeus splendens sp. nov.: A, pygophore, dorsal view; B, pygophore, lateral view; C, right paramere, inner view; D, right paramere, external view. Heraeus tiputini sp. nov.: E, pygophore, dorsal view; F, pygophore, lateral view; G, right paramere, inner view; H, right paramere, external view." pageId="46" pageNumber="75">Fig. 23A, B</figureCitation>
) rounded, anterior margin of dorsal aperture rounded. Parameres: 
<figureCitation box="[286,397,1358,1380]" captionStart="Figure 23" captionStartId="46.[144,223,1062,1081]" captionTargetBox="[148,1420,195,1028]" captionTargetId="figure-272@46.[144,1424,194,1032]" captionTargetPageId="46" captionText="Figure 23. Male genitalia. Heraeus splendens sp. nov.: A, pygophore, dorsal view; B, pygophore, lateral view; C, right paramere, inner view; D, right paramere, external view. Heraeus tiputini sp. nov.: E, pygophore, dorsal view; F, pygophore, lateral view; G, right paramere, inner view; H, right paramere, external view." pageId="46" pageNumber="75">Figure 23</figureCitation>
(C, D). Aedeagus: vesical lobes sclerotized posteriorly, with spines distally; 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="75">processus gonopori</emphasis>
long and slender.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="46.[144,350,1496,1549]" box="[144,283,1496,1517]" pageId="46" pageNumber="75">
